<item>
 <title>My God, it&#039;s full of Games!</title>
 <link>https://www.socallinuxexpo.org/scale9x/presentations/my-god-its-full-games</link>
 <description>&lt;p&gt;It&#039;s easier than ever to run Windows games on Linux... here are easy ways to do it with Wine.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;field field-type-text field-field-track&quot;&gt;
    &lt;div class=&quot;field-items&quot;&gt;
            &lt;div class=&quot;field-item odd&quot;&gt;
                &lt;a href=&quot;category/presentationcategory/general&quot;&gt;General&lt;/a&gt;        &lt;/div&gt;
        &lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;field field-type-text field-field-presentation-short-abs&quot;&gt;
    &lt;div class=&quot;field-items&quot;&gt;
            &lt;div class=&quot;field-item odd&quot;&gt;
                &lt;p&gt;Linux has always been able to run Windows apps using Wine with varying degrees of success, but it often required heavy reading and trying lots of workarounds. This presentation will show how easy it is to install and run games on Linux using package managers like Wine and Winetricks, and show how to contribute a new game script to Winetricks.&lt;/p&gt;
        &lt;/div&gt;
        &lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;field field-type-text field-field-presentation-long-abs&quot;&gt;
    &lt;div class=&quot;field-items&quot;&gt;
            &lt;div class=&quot;field-item odd&quot;&gt;
                &lt;p&gt;Linux has always been able to run Windows apps using Wine with varying degrees of success, but it often required reading lots of web pages and trying lots of workarounds.    But package managers like Winetricks and PlayOnLinux are changing that; they make installing games really easy.  Dan will show how easy it is to install and run games on Linux using Wine and Winetricks, and show how to contribute a new game script to Winetricks.&lt;/p&gt;
        &lt;/div&gt;
        &lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;field field-type-text field-field-presentation-speaker-id&quot;&gt;
